23/01/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Traian Basescu has said the Black Sea region will be a foreign policy priority in 2006. Speaking at a meeting with foreign diplomats in Bucharest Friday (20 January), he noted the region's wealth of energy resources and stressed the need for better security there. He also voiced Romania's willingness to make Russia a partner on Black Sea issues. 
In other news, Transparency International, the leading global anti-corruption organisation, announced on Sunday that it would launch a major campaign to monitor the reform of Romania's judiciary. The organisation would work to increase public awareness about corruption, monitor the judicial panels dealing with graft, and provide help to those who feel they received improper treatment. Justice Minister Monica Macovei welcomed the new project. (Nine o'clock - 23/01/06; Reuters - 22/01/06)
